Bezeq, Cellcom, Partner, Delek, Teva: Israeli Equity Preview

-- B y   G w e n   A c k e r m a n
-- 
2011-07-18T06:43:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-18/bezeq-cellcom-partner-delek-teva-israeli-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in Israeli markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
the company names and prices are from the last close unless
otherwise stated.  The TA-25 Index fell less than 0.1 percent to 1,251.14 in
 Tel Aviv .  Bezeq The Israeli Telecommunication Corp. (BEZQ IT),
 Cellcom Israel Ltd. (CEL)  , Partner Communications Co. (PTNR
IT): The Ministry of Communications set new rules yesterday for
new cellular towers, saying approval for new sites will be
dependent on agreement to let other operators use them. Also, a
ministry committee will meet today to decide whether to allow
Select Communications Ltd. to go ahead and build a wireless
company. Bezeq, the country’s largest telecommunications
company, rose 1.5 percent to 8.586 shekels. Cellcom, the biggest
wireless operator by subscribers, declined 0.9 percent to 90.90
shekels. Partner, the second-largest mobile-phone company, lost
0.9 percent to 51.52 shekels.  Delek Group Ltd. (DLEKG)  : Bonds of the holding company
were reaffirmed at A1 and their outlook was changed to
“negative” from “stable” by Moody’s Midroog. Delek advanced
2 percent to 750 shekels.  Teva Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. (TEVA)  : The world’s
largest generic drugmaker may fire product-development employees
in  Israel , the daily Calcalist reported, without saying where it
got the information. Teva dropped 2.6 percent to 165 shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gwen Ackerman in Jerusalem at 
 gackerman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  